@node "Hide Gadgets" "MegaD v3.1 - by John L. Jones"

Hide gadgets:
============

There are three small, box shaped gadgets on the left side of the
MegaD main window, each of these having a horizontal line through it.

Single-clicking on the upper gadget hides the nine @{"device & command" link "Device & Command Gadgets"}
gadgets.

Single-clicking on the middle gadget will hide the @{"Files Selected" link "Files Selected Area"}
informational area.

Single-clicking on the lower gadget hides the @{"numeric keypad" link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"} gadgets
in the bottom of the MegaD window.

The purpose of these three "hide" gadgets is to allow you to hide areas
of the MegaD window that you may not be concerned about, and as a result,
free up more room to view @{"list area" link "List Area"} information.  The settings of the
hide gadgets are saved so that the next time you run the program, the
main window reflects the conditions of the last session.


