@node "Device & Command Gadgets" "MegaD v3.1 - by John L. Jones"

Device & Command gadgets:
========================

Immediatly above the @{"Device Name" link "Device Name Gadget"} string gadget is a collection of nine
user-defined gadgets.  You can activate these nine gadgets in one of
two ways.  The most obvious way is by single-clicking on them.  You
can also activate them using the 9 numeric gadgets (1-9) on the TOP OF
YOUR KEYBOARD (do not attempt to activate these gadgets using the numeric
keypad on the right side of your keyboard).  The figure below illustrates
which key corresponds to each gadget.


    -----------------------------------------------
   | @{" Free Volumes " link "Free Volumes"} @{"@      Volumes In Memory      " link "Volumes In Memory"} |
   | @{"                                             " link "List Area"} |
   | @{"  " link "Hide Gadgets"} @{"     #1      " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{"      #4      " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{"     #7      " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} |
   |    @{"     #2      " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{"      #5      " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{"     #8   <--" link "Device & Command Gadgets"}---- Device & Command
   |    @{"     #3      " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{"      #6      " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{"     #9      " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} |      Gadgets (9)
   |      Device Name: @{"                           " link "Device Name Gadget"} |
   |     ----------------------------------------  |
   |    | Files Selected           Chip          | |
   |    | Dir.Selected             Fast          | |
   | @{"  " link "Hide Gadgets"} | Bytes Selected           Large         | |<--@{" Files Selected Area " link "Files Selected Area"}
   |    | Free Disk Space          Total         | |
   |    | Active Directory                       | |
   | @{"  " link "Hide Gadgets"}  ----------------------------------------  |
   | @{"          " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"} @{"          " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"} @{"          " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"} @{"          " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"} @{"C" link "Ctrl & Shift & Alt Gadgets"} |
   | @{"          " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"} @{"          " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"} @{"          " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"} @{"          " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"}   |
   | @{"          " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"} @{"          " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"} @{"          " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"} @{"          " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"} @{"S" link "Ctrl & Shift & Alt Gadgets"} |
   | @{"          " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"} @{"          " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"} @{"          " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"}              |
   | @{"                     " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"} @{"          " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"} @{"          " link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"} @{"A" link "Ctrl & Shift & Alt Gadgets"} |
    ------------------------------------------------

You can toggle the function of these gadgets to act as either command
gadgets, or as device gadgets.  Use the MegaD menu item
@{"Utilities" link "Menu Utilities"} / @{"Utilities in Window" link "Menu Utilities - Utilities in Window"} to toggle between the two.

When you have NOT selected the @{"Utilities" link "Menu Utilities"} / @{"Utilities in Window" link "Menu Utilities - Utilities in Window"} menu
item, these nine gadgets act as device gadgets.  In this case, you can
@{"configure" link "Configuring MegaD"} them so that they act as quick access buttons for opening
directory windows.  Lets say you @{"configure" link "Configuring MegaD"} the gadgets as follows:

    -----------------------------------------------
   | @{" Free Volumes " link "Free Volumes"} @{"@      Volumes In Memory      " link "Volumes In Memory"} |
   | @{"                                             " link "List Area"} |
   | @{"  " link "Hide Gadgets"} @{"    df0:     " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{"    Work:     " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{"  DPaintIV:  " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} |
   |    @{"    df1:     " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{"  System2.0:  " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{"   Ram:Env   " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} |
   |    @{"    df2:     " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{"     Ram:     " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{"Work:MyStuff " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} |
   |      Device Name: @{"                           " link "Device Name Gadget"} |
   
In this case, you could open a directory window for "Ram:" by either
clicking on it's gadget, or by selecting the "6" key on the top of
your keyboard.

By selecting the menu item @{"Utilities" link "Menu Utilities"} / @{"Utilities in Window" link "Menu Utilities - Utilities in Window"}, these
nine gadgets will contain the same commands contained in the MegaD
@{"Utilities" link "Menu Utilities"} menu.  If you select @{"Utilities" link "Menu Utilities"} / @{"Utilities in Window" link "Menu Utilities - Utilities in Window"}
under MegaD's default configuration, then these nine gadgets will
contain the following:

    -----------------------------------------------
   | @{" Free Volumes " link "Free Volumes"} @{"@      Volumes In Memory      " link "Volumes In Memory"} |
   | @{"                                             " link "List Area"} |
   | @{"  " link "Hide Gadgets"} @{" LhA    Pack " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{" LhA     Test " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{"    First    " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} |
   |    @{" LhA  UnPack " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{" LhA Recursive" link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{"    Next     " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} |
   |    @{" LhA    List " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{" Copy/Format  " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} @{"   Previous  " link "Device & Command Gadgets"} |
   |      Device Name: @{"                           " link "Device Name Gadget"} |

In this configuration, these nine gadgets no longer open directory
windows.  Rather, they perform commands similar to those possible
using the @{"Utilities" link "Menu Utilities"} menu.


