When you use the <Set Export> command, the following window opens.
This allows you to set the paramaters desired for a database export.
For a thorough discussion of this feature, refer to the @{"Export File" link "Command Export File"}
built-in command or the @{"Output" link "Menu Output"} / @{"Database Export File" link "Command Export File"} menu item.


 -----------------------------------------------------------------
| @{"  " link "Set Export - File Attribute Fields"} Filename    maximum size  30          Field Separator        |
| @{"  " link "Set Export - File Attribute Fields"} Volume Name maximum size  30               @{"     " link "Set Export - Field & Record Separators"}             |
| @{"  " link "Set Export - File Attribute Fields"} Path        maximum size 180         Record  Separator       |
| @{"  " link "Set Export - File Attribute Fields"} Type                size   4               @{"     " link "Set Export - Field & Record Separators"}             |
| @{"  " link "Set Export - File Attribute Fields"} Date                size  18         Filename for path       |
| @{"  " link "Set Export - File Attribute Fields"} Size                size   8   @{"                             " link "Set Export - Filename for Path"} |
| @{"  " link "Set Export - File Attribute Fields"} Blocks used         size   8                                 |
| @{"  " link "Set Export - File Attribute Fields"} Protection          size   8   @{"@  Export Directory & Files  " link "Set Export - Export Directories & Files"} |
| @{"  " link "Set Export - File Attribute Fields"} Comment     maximum size  80   @{"@     Overwrite old file     "link "Set Export - Overwrite Or Append Old File"} |
|           @{"    Use    " link "Main"}                       @{"  Cancel  " link "Main"}          |
 -----------------------------------------------------------------


