@node "Set Export - File Attribute Fields" "MegaD v3.1 - by John L. Jones"

@{" Set Export " link "Command Set Export"} - File Attribute Fields:
====================================

You will find 9 separate file attribute gadgets on the left side of the
@{"Set Export window" link "Command Set Export"}.  Select those attributes that you want included in
your database.  It's important that you think this part out thoroughly.
Some database programs are rigid, allowing very little changing once the
database is started.  Others allow you to add new fields to an already
created database.  

MegaD lists the maximum field size to the right of each attribute.  If
you create your database with fields that are smaller than those listed,
you may either lose information, or your database may not accept the
export file.


See Also:   @{" Export File                  " link "Command Export File"} built-in command
            @{" Output " link "Menu Output"} / @{" Database Export File " link "Command Export File"} menu item
            @{" Set Export                   " link "Command Set Export"} built-in command
            @{" Export Directories & Files   " link "Set Export - Export Directories & Files"} set export window item
            @{" Field & Record Separators    " link "Set Export - Field & Record Separators"} set export window item
            @{" Filename for Path            " link "Set Export - Filename for Path"} set export window item
            @{" Overwrite Or Append Old File " link "Set Export - Overwrite Or Append Old File"} set export window item

@endnode

@node "Set Export - Field & Record Separators" "MegaD v3.1 - by John L. Jones"

@{" Set Export " link "Command Set Export"} - Field/Record Separators:
======================================
On the right side of the window, you will find two integer string gadgets.
One is titled <Field Separator>, the other is titled <Record Separator>.
Both require that you know the ASCII value of the character separating
your fields and your records (as defined by your database).  MegaD defaults
to the standard used by most databases.  The value for the Field Separator
is 44 (which is the ASCII value of a comma).  The value for the Record
Separator is 10 (which is the value of a return character).


See Also:   @{" Export File                  " link "Command Export File"} built-in command
            @{" Output " link "Menu Output"} / @{" Database Export File " link "Command Export File"} menu item
            @{" Set Export                   " link "Command Set Export"} built-in command
            @{" Export Directories & Files   " link "Set Export - Export Directories & Files"} set export window item
            @{" File Attribute Fields        " link "Set Export - File Attribute Fields"} set export window item
            @{" Filename for Path            " link "Set Export - Filename for Path"} set export window item
            @{" Overwrite Or Append Old File " link "Set Export - Overwrite Or Append Old File"} set export window item

@endnode

@node "Set Export - Filename for Path" "MegaD v3.1 - by John L. Jones"

@{" Set Export " link "Command Set Export"} - Filename for path string gadget:
==============================================
You have already told MegaD the path into which you'd like to place the
export file (you did this by choosing a @{"DEST" link "DEST Gadget"} directory earlier).  Now you
must tell MegaD what to name the export file.  Do so in this string gadget.
I do want to stress, only put the filename (not the whole path) inside
this gadget, since the path has already been defined.


See Also:   @{" Export File                  " link "Command Export File"} built-in command
            @{" Output " link "Menu Output"} / @{" Database Export File " link "Command Export File"} menu item
            @{" Set Export                   " link "Command Set Export"} built-in command
            @{" Export Directories & Files   " link "Set Export - Export Directories & Files"} set export window item
            @{" Field & Record Separators    " link "Set Export - Field & Record Separators"} set export window item
            @{" File Attribute Fields        " link "Set Export - File Attribute Fields"} set export window item
            @{" Overwrite Or Append Old File " link "Set Export - Overwrite Or Append Old File"} set export window item

@endnode

@node "Set Export - Export Directories & Files" "MegaD v3.1 - by John L. Jones"

@{" Set Export " link "Command Set Export"} - Export Directories & Files cycle gadget:
======================================================
This gadget has three options.

   <Export Directories & Files>,
   <Export Files only>, and
   <Export Directories only>.

The function of this gadget should be self explanatory.


See Also:   @{" Export File                  " link "Command Export File"} built-in command
            @{" Output " link "Menu Output"} / @{" Database Export File " link "Command Export File"} menu item
