@node "Command TX Find" "MegaD v3.1 - by John L. Jones"

'TX Find' command:
=================

Allows you to search for a text string within the most recently selected
MegaD @{"text-viewer" link "MegaD Text-Viewer"} text window.  This command has no effect when there are
no MegaD @{"text-viewer" link "MegaD Text-Viewer"} windows open.

When you select <TX Find>, MegaD opens a window similar to the following:

    ----------------------------------
   |  Enter the string to search for  |
   |                                  |
   |        ?, #?, * permitted        |
   |----------------------------------|
   |           Search String          |
   |  ------------------------------  |
   | |                              | |
   |  ------------------------------  |
   |  -----                 --------  |
   | | Use |               | Cancel | |
   |  -----                 --------  |
    ----------------------------------

Enter the string that you'd like to find (pattern match symbols
are acceptable), and select the <Use> gadget.  MegaD will highlight
all occurrances of that string.

To scroll forward through each occurrance of the string, use the
@{"TX RepeatFind" link "Command TX RepeatFind"} command.


See Also:   @{" TX RepeatFind    " link "Command TX RepeatFind"} built-in command

@endnode

