@node "Prefs Display - Date Format" "MegaD v3.1 - by John L. Jones"

@{" Prefs Display " link "Prefs Display"} - Date Format:
=============================

The <Date Format> cycle gadget specifies what format you would
like MegaD to display all dates.  Possibilities include:

   mm/dd/yy    05-30-93
   dd/mm/yy    30-05-93
   yy/mmm/dd   93-05-30
   dd/mmm/yy   30-May-93



See Also:   @{" Display                    " link "Prefs Display"} preference window
            @{" Use Today Yesterday        " link "Prefs Display - Use Today Yesterday"} display preference
            @{" Menu Show " link "Menu Show"} / @{" Date " link "Menu Show - Date"} menu item
            @{" Display Memory, Date, Time " link "Prefs Defaults - Display Memory, Date, Time"} defaults preference

@endnode

@node "Prefs Display - 1000 Separator" "MegaD v3.1 - by John L. Jones"

@{" Prefs Display " link "Prefs Display"} - 1000 Separator:
================================

The <1000 Seperator> cycle gadget specifies what format you would
like MegaD to use when displaying numbers.  Possibilities include:

   1,000,000
   1.000.000
   1 000 000
     1000000

Each of the above examples represents one million.



See Also:   @{" Display " link "Prefs Display"} preference window

@endnode

@node "Prefs Display - Use Today Yesterday" "MegaD v3.1 - by John L. Jones"

@{" Prefs Display " link "Prefs Display"} - Use Today Yesterday:
=====================================

When <Use today/yesterday> is selected, MegaD displays files created
today and yesterday with the strings "Today" and "Yesterday", instead
of using the normal date string.

Additionally, MegaD will display file creation dates between 2 days
and 7 days prior, with "Sunday", "Monday", "Tuesday", etc.

Any file created greater than 7 days prior will use the standard
date string.

This feature functions only under Workbench 2.0 or higher.


See Also:   @{" Display                    " link "Prefs Display"} preference window
            @{" Date Format                " link "Prefs Display - Date Format"} display preference
            @{" Menu Show " link "Menu Show"} / @{" Date " link "Menu Show - Date"} menu item
            @{" Display Memory, Date, Time " link "Prefs Defaults - Display Memory, Date, Time"} defaults preference

@endnode

@node "Prefs Display - 12 Hour Clock" "MegaD v3.1 - by John L. Jones"

@{" Prefs Display " link "Prefs Display"} - 12 Hour Clock:
===============================

When <12 Hour Clock> is selected, MegaD display's time using
hours 1-12 and AM/PM.

When <12 Hour Clock> is not selected, MegaD displays time
using hours 00-23, and omits AM/PM.



See Also:   @{" Display                    " link "Prefs Display"} preference window
            @{" Menu Show " link "Menu Show"} / @{" Date " link "Menu Show - Date"} menu item
            @{" Display Memory, Date, Time " link "Prefs Defaults - Display Memory, Date, Time"} defaults preference

@endnode

@node "Prefs Display - Decimal Is Comma" "MegaD v3.1 - by John L. Jones"

@{" Prefs Display " link "Prefs Display"} - Decimal Is Comma:
==================================

Since MegaD doesn't display floating point information, this gadget
has no effect.  It is included in the event MegaD ever needs to
display decimal points.



See Also:   @{" Display " link "Prefs Display"} preference window

@endnode

@node "Prefs Display - Directory Listing Order" "MegaD v3.1 - by John L. Jones"

@{" Prefs Display " link "Prefs Display"} - Directory Listing Order:
=========================================

The <Directory Listing Order> cycle gadget controls whether files are
listed before, after, or intermixed with directories within the
@{"directory windows" link "Directory Windows"}.

The following possibilities exist:

   List directories first
   List files first
   List items mixed
   


See Also:   @{" Display " link "Prefs Display"} preference window

@endnode

@node "Prefs Display - Order Of File Information" "MegaD v3.1 - by John L. Jones"

@{" Prefs Display " link "Prefs Display"} - Order Of File Information:
===========================================

<Order of file information> incorporates five separate cycle gadgets,
labelled <Name>, <Size>, <Date>, <Protection> and <Comment>.

Using these gadgets, you can specify the order in which MegaD displays
these items inside @{"directory windows" link "Directory Windows"}.  Items will be listed with the
lowest numbered item to the left, and the highest numbered item to the
right of @{"directory windows" link "Directory Windows"}.

NOTE:  Simply because these items are numbered doesn't mean that they
       will necessarily be displayed inside @{"directory windows" link "Directory Windows"}.  Use
       MegaD's @{"show menu" link "Menu Show"}  to toggle these items on and off inside
       @{"directory windows" link "Directory Windows"}.



See Also:   @{" Display " link "Prefs Display"} preference window
            @{" Show    " link "Menu Show"} menu
            
            
            
            

@endnode

@node "Prefs Keypads" "MegaD v3.1 - by John L. Jones"

'Keypads' preferences - Built In's:
==================================

This window is one of the most powerful within MegaD.  I'll try to describe
it's major features:


 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
| @{" ABoot Add  " link "PK - Command"} @{"Clr Pattern" link "PK - Command"} @{"Create Dir " link "PK - Command"} @{" Filters + " link "PK - Command"} @{"   Label   " link "PK - Command"} @{"Output File" link "PK - Command"}  |
| @{" ABoot Edit " link "PK - Command"} @{"  Clr Src  " link "PK - Command"} @{"  Delete   " link "PK - Command"} @{" Filters - " link "PK - Command"} @{"Label Align" link "PK - Command"} @{"Output Prt " link "PK - Command"}  |
| @{" Clear All  " link "PK - Command"} @{" ClrSrcDir " link "PK - Command"} @{"DirCloseWin" link "PK - Command"} @{"   Find    " link "PK - Command"} @{"Label Times" link "PK - Command"} @{"Print Spool" link "PK - Command"}  |
| @{" Close Wind " link "PK - Command"} @{"ClrSrcFile " link "PK - Command"} @{"DirOpenWind" link "PK - Command"} @{"Free Volume" link "PK - Command"} @{"   Move    " link "PK - Command"} @{" Prt Text  " link "PK - Command"}  |
| @{" Clr ABoot  " link "PK - Command"} @{"   Copy    " link "PK - Command"} @{" Duplicate " link "PK - Command"} @{"  Go Deep  " link "PK - Command"} @{" Move As   " link "PK - Command"} @{"   Quit    " link "PK - Command"}  |
| @{"  Clr Dir   " link "PK - Command"} @{"  Copy As  " link "PK - Command"} @{"Export File" link "PK - Command"} @{"  Iconify  " link "PK - Command"} @{"Open Window" link "PK - Command"} @{"  Relabel  " link "PK - Command"}  |
| @{" Clr Files  " link "PK - Command"} @{"Copy/Format" link "PK - Command"} @{"File Commen" link "PK - Command"} @{"Lab. Modify" link "PK - Command"} @{"  Open...  " link "PK - Command"} @{"  Rename   " link "PK - Command"}  |
| @{"@    Page 1      " link "Prefs Keypads - Page"}                                                         |
|                      @{"            " link "PK - Num"} @{"           " link "PK - Num"} @{"           " link "PK - Num"} @{"           " link "PK - Num"} @{" C " link "PK - CSA"} |
| @{"@   Built In's   " link "Prefs Keypads - Menu Sets"}    @{"            " link "PK - Num"} @{"           " link "PK - Num"} @{"           " link "PK - Num"} @{"           " link "PK - Num"}     |
| @{"  Add  " link "Prefs Keypads - Add"} @{" Delete  " link "Prefs Keypads - Delete"}    @{"            " link "PK - Num"} @{"           " link "PK - Num"} @{"           " link "PK - Num"} @{"           " link "PK - Num"} @{" S " link "PK - CSA"} |
| @{"     Modify      " link "Prefs Keypads - Modify"}    @{"            " link "PK - Num"} @{"           " link "PK - Num"} @{"           " link "PK - Num"}                 |
|                      @{"                        " link "PK - Num"} @{"           " link "PK - Num"} @{"           " link "PK - Num"} @{" A " link "PK - CSA"} |
|                                                                           |
| @{"    Hot  Key     " link "Prefs Keypads - Hot Key"}        @{"         Use        " link "Preferences Window"} @{"       Cancel      " link "Preferences Window"}         |
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

   Configuring Numeric Keypad Gadgets:
   ==================================
   
   In the lower right corner of the window is a representation of the
   @{"numeric keypad gadgets" link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"}.  You can configure any command available in
   the upper portion of this window onto these @{"numeric keypad gadgets" link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"}.
   
   Merely single-click on the desired command so that it is highlighted.
   Then single-click on the desired numeric keypad gadget in the lower
   right of this window.  Voila!!  That numeric keypad gadget is now
   configured with that command.
   
   
   
   General:
   =======
   
   By clicking on the <Built-In> cycle gadget in the middle left side of
   the window, you will cycle through all of the  @{"7 different types of gadgets" link "7 Gadget Types"}.
   
   You can create gadgets using the @{"Add Gadget" link "Prefs Keypads - Add"} and then configure them
   into the @{"numeric keypad gadgets" link "Numeric Keypad Gadgets"}.
   
   You can alter certain types of gadgets, incuding gadget names and colors
   using the @{"Modify Gadget" link "Prefs Keypads - Modify"}.
   
   You can remove gadgets using the @{"Delete gadget" link "Prefs Keypads - Delete"}.
   
   Finally, you can assign gadgets a @{"Hot Key" link "Prefs Keypads - Hot Key"}, which will automatically
   execute that command upon the press of a key.
   
   
   This has shown what the keypads preferences window will look like when
   the command type cycle gadget is set to <Built In's>.  There are 6 other
   types of commands though.  You can access the following command types
   by clicking on the cycle gadget labelled <Built-In's>:

   @{" ARexx Gadgets       " link "ARexx Gadgets"}
   @{" AutoBoots           " link "AutoBoots"}
   @{" Device Gadgets      " link "Device Gadgets"}
   @{" Gadget Sets         " link "Gadget Sets"}
   @{" Menu Sets           " link "Menu Sets"}
   @{" User Gadgets        " link "User Gadgets"}


See Also:   @{" Built-In Commands " link "Built-In Commands"}

@endnode

