@node "Gadget Set - Inner Window Width" "MegaD v3.1 - by John L. Jones"

@{" Gadget Set Window " link "Gadget Set Window"} - Inner Window Width:
========================================

Enter the width (in pixels) that you'd desire for this gadget set.
The inner window width is the total width of the window minus the
width of the left and right borders.

Immediately to the right of the <Inner Window Width> integer gadget,
MegaD lists the minimum and maximum acceptable values for the <Inner
Window Width>.  These values are based upon your screen's width.

Perhaps an easier way to define the dimensions of the @{"gadget set" link "Gadget Sets"}
is to use the @{"'close sizing gadget'" link "Gadget Set - Close Sizing Gadget"} located immediately
below the "Window Type" cycle gadget in the @{"Gadget Set" link "Gadget Set Window"}
definition window.



See Also:   @{" Gadget Set                       " link "Gadget Set Window"} definition window
            @{" Gadget Set - Close Sizing Gadget " link "Gadget Set - Close Sizing Gadget"} discussion
            @{" Gadget Set - Inner Window Height " link "Gadget Set - Inner Window Height"} definition
            @{" Keypads - Gadget Sets            " link "Prefs Keypads - Gadget Sets"} preference window
            @{" Gadget Sets                      " link "Gadget Sets"} discussion

@endnode

@node "Gadget Set - Inner Window Height" "MegaD v3.1 - by John L. Jones"

@{" Gadget Set Window " link "Gadget Set Window"} - Inner Window Height:
=========================================

Enter the height (in pixels) that you'd desire for this gadget set.
The inner window height is the total height of the window minus the
height of the top and bottom borders.

Immediately to the right of the <Inner Window Height> integer gadget,
MegaD lists the minimum and maximum acceptable values for the <Inner
Window Height>.  These values are based upon your screen's height.

Perhaps an easier way to define the dimensions of the @{"gadget set" link "Gadget Sets"}
is to use the @{"'close sizing gadget'" link "Gadget Set - Close Sizing Gadget"} located immediately
below the "Window Type" cycle gadget in the @{"Gadget Set" link "Gadget Set Window"}
definition window.


See Also:   @{" Gadget Set                      " link "Gadget Set Window"} definition window
            @{" Gadget Set - Close Sizing Gadget " link "Gadget Set - Close Sizing Gadget"} discussion
            @{" Gadget Set - Inner Window Width " link "Gadget Set - Inner Window Width"} definition
            @{" Keypads - Gadget Sets           " link "Prefs Keypads - Gadget Sets"} preference window
            @{" Gadget Sets                     " link "Gadget Sets"} discussion

@endnode

